<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" class="marketing">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta name="description" content="How Very Good AdBlock blocks ads: Manifest V3 network rules, source-level YouTube and Twitch ad removal, pop-up defusing, and one-click local controls. Chrome and Firefox, no telemetry.">
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#100a0b">
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://verygoodadblock.org/features/">
    <script>
      // Set the theme before first paint (no flash): saved choice, else system.
      (function () {
        try {
          var saved = localStorage.getItem('vga-theme')
          var theme = saved || (matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: light)').matches ? 'light' : 'dark')
          document.documentElement.dataset.theme = theme
        }
        catch (e) {}
      })()
    </script>
    <meta property="og:type" content="website">
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="Very Good AdBlock">
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://verygoodadblock.org/features/">
    <meta property="og:title" content="Features — Very Good AdBlock">
    <meta property="og:description" content="Four layers of protection: network blocking, YouTube and Twitch ad removal at the source, pop-up defusing, and one-click local controls.">
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://verygoodadblock.org/icons/icon-128.png">
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="48x48" href="/icons/icon-48.png">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/icons/icon.svg">
    <title>Features — Very Good AdBlock</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
  </head>
  <body class="marketing-shell">
    @include('nav')

    <main id="top">
      <section class="features-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Features</p>
        <h1>Four layers, one quiet browser.</h1>
        <p class="hero-lede">Very Good AdBlock stops ads at the source instead of patching the page after they load. Each layer has its own page with the exact detail. Pick where you want to start.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="feature-index" aria-label="All features">
        <a class="feature-index-card" href="/features/network-blocking/">
          <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 3 4 6v5c0 4.4 3.1 8.3 8 9.5 4.9-1.2 8-5.1 8-9.5V6l-8-3Z"></path><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"></path></svg></span>
          <h2>Network blocking</h2>
          <p>Manifest V3 declarative rules stop 14,000+ ad, tracker, and annoyance hosts before the request completes, with zero per-request JavaScript.</p>
          <span class="feature-more">Explore network blocking →</span>
        </a>
        <a class="feature-index-card" href="/features/youtube-twitch/">
          <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="14" rx="3"></rect><path d="m10 9 5 3-5 3V9Z"></path></svg></span>
          <h2>YouTube and Twitch</h2>
          <p>Strips ads out of YouTube's player response before they schedule, skips what slips through, and detects Twitch stream ads. The real video never breaks.</p>
          <span class="feature-more">Explore video ad removal →</span>
        </a>
        <a class="feature-index-card" href="/features/popups/">
          <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="14" rx="2"></rect><path d="M3 9h18"></path><path d="m9.5 12.5 5 5M14.5 12.5l-5 5"></path></svg></span>
          <h2>Pop-ups and pop-unders</h2>
          <p>Neutralizes the click-hijack windows streaming and file-host sites open, including the ones fired from inside a player iframe, and keeps the ones you asked for.</p>
          <span class="feature-more">Explore pop-up defusing →</span>
        </a>
        <a class="feature-index-card" href="/features/controls/">
          <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M4 8h10M18 8h2M4 16h2M10 16h10"></path><circle cx="16" cy="8" r="2.4"></circle><circle cx="8" cy="16" r="2.4"></circle></svg></span>
          <h2>Control and privacy</h2>
          <p>Pause per site, keep an allowlist, hide cookie banners, and read local stats from a clean dashboard. Nothing about your browsing leaves your machine.</p>
          <span class="feature-more">Explore controls and privacy →</span>
        </a>
      </section>

      @include('browsers-band')
      @include('subscribe')
    </main>

    @include('footer')
  </body>
</html>
